HEADWORD: Contrivement
<hw>Con*trive"ment</hw> <pr>(?)</pr>, <pos>n.</pos> <def>Contrivance;
invention; arrangement; design; plan.</def> <mark>[Obs.]</mark>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><q>Consider the admirable <qex>contrivement</qex> and artifice of
this great fabric.</q> <rj><qau>Glanvill.</qau></rj>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><q>Active to meet their <qex>contrivements</qex>.</q> <rj><qau>Sir G.
Buck.</qau></rj>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><ent>Contriver</ent>⟦br⟧
